 } } \right]\,$$ are 
<img class="question-image" src="https://imagex.cdn.examgoal.net/SELaz94YDuuXYGowP/RnskxGDrcGSCkfjkWRXnfaYoPE9GK/BWJUCnPRrPUcge86KCtb7u/uploadfile.jpg" loading="lazy" alt="GATE ECE 2004 Network Theory - Two Port Networks Question 30 English">

explanation:
Appling KVL in given circuit
<br/><br/>$$
\begin{aligned}
&V_i(s)=I(s)\left\langle R+s L+\frac{1}{s c}\right\rangle \\\\
&V_i(s)=\frac{I(s)}{s c}\left(s^2 L C+s C R+1\right) \\\\
&V_0(s)=\frac{I(s)}{S C} \\\\
&\therefore \frac{V_0(s)}{V_i(s)}=\frac{1}{s^2 L C+s C R+1}=\frac{\frac{1}{L C}}{s^2+\frac{L}{R} s+\frac{1}{L C}} \\\\
&\frac{V_0(s)}{V_i(s)}=\frac{10^6}{s^2+10^6 s+10^6}
\end{aligned}
$$

